      • GraphmlReader

        public GraphmlReader(java.lang.String file)
        Reader used to read graphml file formats. It receives the path to the file, reads its contents and generates a Jung Graph. It relies on GraphMLReader from Thinkerpop
        Parameters:
        file - The url to the source file

      • getJungDirectedGraph

        public edu.uci.ics.jung.graph.DirectedSparseMultigraph<Node,Edge> getJungDirectedGraph(java.lang.String[] nestedAttributesOrder,
                                                                                       java.lang.String[] nodeLabelAttributes,
                                                                                       java.lang.String[] edgeImportAttributes,
                                                                                       boolean saveCategoricalAttributes)
        GENERAL METHOD TO GET THE JUNG GRAPH
        Parameters:
        nestedAttributesOrder - the ordered vector of node attributes
        nodeLabelAttributes - the vector of node attributes
        edgeImportAttributes - the vector of edge attributes
        saveCategoricalAttributes - true if you want to save the categorical attributes in the general collection of attributes stored in Mapper Class. The collection does not accept duplicates. Enabling this might occupy a big chunk of memory because for instance all the node names will be stored in the collection
        Returns:
        THE JUNG GRAPH as DirectedSparseMultigraph
